      "id": 1,
      "text": "Boston was founded on Shawmut Peninsula in 1630 by English Puritan settlers, who named the city after Boston, Lincolnshire in England.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boston"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Puritan ethics and a focus on education led to Boston Latin School’s founding in 1635, America’s first public school.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5,
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boston"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1852, Boston Public Library opened as the first free library in the United States.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boston"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Logan International Airport in East Boston is the city’s principal airport.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8
